Task: fix 2 bugs in app/scramble_view.cpp

--- BUG 1: background not jet black ---
All TColorRGB background values in scramble_view.cpp are dark grey (30,30,40) or (25,25,35).
Change ALL background TColorRGB values to (0,0,0) — pure jet black.
Foreground colours stay the same. Only change the second argument of TColorAttr where it is a background.
Lines to check: ~269-286, ~474-476, ~563-568. Search: rg -n 'TColorRGB.*[23][05]' app/scramble_view.cpp

--- BUG 2: tall→smol toggle leaves outer border of tall window ---
Root cause: setDisplayState(sdsSmol) calls layoutChildren() which resizes child views,
but never resizes the TScrambleWindow itself. The window stays at tall height.

Fix: in setDisplayState(), after calling layoutChildren(), resize the window to the 
correct height for the new state.

First, find the smol and tall window sizes:
  rg -n 'kSmol\|kTall\|kCat\|kInput\|smolH\|tallH' app/scramble_view.h app/scramble_view.cpp

Then in setDisplayState(), after layoutChildren():
- If switching to sdsSmol: resize window to smol dimensions using growTo() or changeBounds()
- If switching to sdsTall: resize window to tall dimensions

Use the existing size constants. If none exist, derive smol height from kCatViewHeight + 2
(for the TWindow frame), and tall height from the existing tall spawn size.
Check how the window is initially sized (find the TScrambleWindow constructor or spawn function)
to get the right values.

